                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5122/40</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-19">May 19,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 494</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 932
                    of April 11, 1931, in regard to the collection of a house tax from American
                    citizens at Tsinan.</p>
                <p>The action taken by the American Consul at Tsinan, as stated in your despatch
                    under acknowledgment, is approved.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>W. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
